newClient

public Client newClient()
Creates a new Client for connecting to servers with. If there is an error creating the client, null will be returned. The default ClientListener will be added to the client if non-null.

Specified by:

The reference to the newly created client, or null.

getServers

public java.util.Set<Server> getServers()

public ClientListener getClientListener()

getSelector

public Selector getSelector()
Returns the selector used by the pipeline to allocate workers for clients and acceptors for servers. This is also used by the servers to create workers to handle clients unless changed explicitly for a given server.

Specified by:
getSelector in interface Pipeline
Returns:
The reference to the Selector.

addProtocol

public <D> void addProtocol(Protocol<D> protocol)
Adds the protocol to the pipeline. A protocol is mapped by a class type, when a client has to read data it queries its pipeline with its current protocol type and proceeds to decode read data.

Specified by:
addProtocol in interface Pipeline
Type Parameters:
D - The data type encoded and decoded by the protocol.
Parameters:
protocol - The protocol to use to encode and decode the given data type.
